   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Year 14 of Lucius Septimius Severus Pius Pertinax and Marcus Aurelius Antoninus Pius, Augusti, and Publius Septimius Geta Caesar Augustus, Phaophi 20. Paid to Apion, nomarches of the Arsinoite nome, acting through his representative Sphyris also called Theon, for the ten-percent tax on calves, by the priests, for the village of Tebtunis, for the receipts of the same year, twenty drachmas, that is, 20 dr.</ab>
